metadata.name: Mis Flores Artificiales
metadata.description:
Mis Flores Artificiales is a series of turning the camera upon oneself as a self healing journey of trust and inner peace. 

Norma Córdova’s image based work creates illusions that conjure the realms of the imagination without presenting a factual reality. They intersect femininity, self identity, and wonder. 

In moody, narrative-driven compositions, Cordova explores desire and desirability, and question the myriad expectations of women and how we are portrayed.
